<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Henry, Alexander. Travels in the Red River Department (Abridged), 1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0024</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">72</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">proves that it is not injurious to health<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">In the winter and in dry seasons the wa<span class="AddHand-editors">[ter]</span> becomes clearer in those times the natives <span class="AddHand-editors">[a]</span>re known to mix clay with their drink<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  When this water is put into a vessel and allowed to settle it will generally produce an Inch of Sediments.  We soon got accustomed to the use of it and found it both sweet and palatable<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  About dusk we returned to our old quarters.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday 28<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This morning having finally settled our accounts with our host &#8212; and having provided provisions for our Journey homewards, composed of parched corn pounded into meal and fat mixed formed into Balls the size of an Egg and ready for use.  We were ferred a cross the Missisouri with our horses<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In leaving the South Side we were sincerely pleased at parting with a set of hypocrites<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Who are led by that cheat Jussiaume a cunning old Frenchman.  But I must except my Host and family from sharing in this reproach for I found them honest, kind and good.  They made me promise that if I returned that I would take my lodging with them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:right;"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">M</span><span class="AddHand-author"><sup>r</sup></span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[76]</span></p>

